Ford May Build China Plant If Venture Ends, 21st Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-02-16T07:34:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/ford-may-build-china-plant-if-venture-ends-21st-says-update1-.html
  Ford Motor Co . may build a new plant
in  China  if its current joint venture with  Mazda Motor Corp . and
Chongqing Changan Automobile Co. ends, the 21st Century Herald
newspaper reported today, citing people it didn’t identify.  The Dearborn, Michigan-based automaker may use Tianjin as a
possible factory location, the newspaper said, without saying
where it got its information.  Trevor Hale, Ford’s Shanghai-based spokesman, said the
automaker has "nothing to announce at this time."  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kae Inoue at 
 kinoue@bloomberg.net  